The paper deals with the Metric Dimension problem, which is a problem in discrete mathematics and graph theory. The paper also specifically focuses on the parameterized complexity of the problem with respect to treewidth, which is a measure of the "tree-likeness" of a graph. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
